hints_latex:
Set

\begin{align*}
A = \left[\begin{array}{cc}
a & b \\ c & d
\end{array}\right]
\end{align*} and calculate

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{cc}
a & b \\ c & d
\end{array}\right] \left[\begin{array}{c} s\\t \end{array}\right]
\end{align*}
Matching one-by-one will give you the values of \emph{a}, \emph{b},
\emph{c} and \emph{d}.

sols_latex:
Following the hint gives us

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{cc}
a & b \\ c & d
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{c} s\\t \end{array}\right] &= \left[\begin{array}{c} as+bt \\ cs+dt \end{array}\right] = s\left[\begin{array}{c} a \\ c\end{array}\right] + t\left[\begin{array}{c} b \\ d\end{array}\right]
\end{align*} Comparing to the original equation gives

\begin{align*}
A = \left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & 3 \\ 2 & -1
\end{array}\right]
\end{align*}

